    "title": "",
    "depth": 0,
    "paragraphs": [
      {
        "sentences": [
          {
            "text": "The Support role is to aid and help protect your allies in any situation.",
            "formatting": {
              "bold": [
                "Support"
              ]
            }
          },
          {
            "text": "Your role is is to shield or heal them, to tanking some damage or sacrificing yourself to keep others alive."
          },
          {
            "text": "You are often giving up the glorious kills in the game to support others, but in the end its usually the support to secure the true MVP award."
          },
          {
            "text": "Support heroes usually lane with Marksman-type Heroes in top lane or at mid lane in order to be able to travel quickly where they are needed.",
            "links": [
              {
                "type": "internal",
                "page": "Heroes"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "sentences": [
          {
            "text": "Support is a type of role that provides some kind of benefit to their team."
          },
          {
            "text": "These benefits provide sustainability through healing or giving shields or deal some form of CC like stunning enemies."
          },
          {
            "text": "They often accompany carry heroes to help them level up faster."
          },
          {
            "text": "They are recommended to participate in team fights to help teammates in accomplishing objectives and not to solo a lane."
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
